@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances/{managedInstanceName}/securityAlertPolicies/{securityAlertPolicyName}
@desc Get a managed server's threat detection policy.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., managedInstanceName: any # The name of the managed instance., securityAlertPolicyName: any # The name of the security alert policy., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@returns(200) Successfully retrieved the managed server threat detection policy.

@endpoint PUT /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances/{managedInstanceName}/securityAlertPolicies/{securityAlertPolicyName}
@desc Creates or updates a threat detection policy.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., managedInstanceName: any # The name of the managed instance., securityAlertPolicyName: any # The name of the security alert policy., parameters: map # The managed server security alert policy., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
@returns(200) Successfully updated the threat detection policy.
@returns(202) Created request to set the server threat detection policy.

@endpoint GET /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances/{managedInstanceName}/securityAlertPolicies
@desc Get the managed server's threat detection policies.
@required {resourceGroupName: any # The name of the resource group that contains the resource. You can obtain this value from the Azure Resource Manager API or the portal., managedInstanceName: any # The name of the managed instance., subscriptionId: any # The subscription ID that identifies an Azure subscription., api-version: any # The API version to use for the request.}
